        [
          "The mortal childe of one Toreador, you were Embraced by their rival. You escaped to LA to get away from their never-ending rivalry.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "POT"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Was the mortal child of an up and coming Toreador. As your father rose in power with the court, you were embraced by a rival of that Toreador. So your sire and your father have been at odds your whole existence. The conflict had become so intense that you were afraid for one of their deaths. This prompted you to move to Los Angeles to escape their conflict. Since coming here, you havegained some influence in the local media, to keep a connection with the art scene as well as protecting the Masquerade. \n\nUnfortunately, your sire didn't appreciate you running away. He has a price out on your head. Lucky for you he's not a prince, so he can't call a blood hunt, but should he wish to make it an issue, the law can be twisted on his side. You are far enough away he can't get to you, but that's not to say he doesn't have people out hunting you, and you know it. You evaded one such hunter in Denver several years ago. You are in LA, as far as you can go, and you've built a life for yourself. You have spun your meager influences into something respectable in the local news and perhaps you can even gain respect in your clan as well. But, you are always looking over your shoulder, waiting for the other shoe to drop. You want security...and in the end, you really always sided with your father anyway. It would be nice if your sire was dead."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Melville Primogen in St. Louis",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Toreador - Entranced by Art"
